Japan's Yamaichi Securities Co. Ltd. announced  Wednesday a pre-tax profit of 17.9 billion yen (174 million dollars) for the  year to March, reversing a loss of 37.4 billion yen a year earlier.
The country's fourth-largest securities company said operating revenue  climbed 25 percent to 236 billion yen in the same period.
Yamaichi forecast a further increase in earnings to 25 billion yen for the  current year with revenue climbing to 245 billion yen.
The company also halved its consolidated pre-tax forecast for the year  just ended from 22 billion yen to 11 billion yen. Group revenue is projected  at 280 billion yen, down from 325 billion yen predicted earlier.
